<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-26T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="621" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.52/2345: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-26T16:00:00-05:00">October 26, 1937—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>210. Reference telegram October 23, 9 a.m. from Guaymas.<note n="30" xml:id="d621fn30">Not printed.</note> Please look into point raised
                            by Yepis that decision to dotate eight instead of four hectares of Yaqui
                            Valley land to each applicant for land is illegal. Presumably Vice
                            Consul has in mind article 47 of Agrarian Code, and the Department
                            understands that land in question is irrigated.</p>
                        <p>If you consider point well taken please take up matter with appropriate
                            authorities.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>